Makes sense. Concrete fix: either remove `validateSchema` if not needed, or implement real key/type checks against the schema contract. Example lightweight runtime validation:

```ts
type PrimitiveType = "string" | "number" | "boolean"
type SimpleSchema = Record<string, PrimitiveType>

export function validateSchema(
  data: Record<string, unknown>,
  schema: SimpleSchema,
): boolean {
  return Object.entries(schema).every(([key, expected]) => {
    const value = data[key]
    return typeof value === expected
  })
}
```

If the codebase already uses a validator (e.g. Zod/Ajv), better to replace this helper with that library for stronger guarantees.

